15
November
Accra Central Branch & Treasury Department Emerge Service Excellence Award Winners.

Accra Central business offices and the Treasury department emerged the proud winners of the coveted Service Excellence Awards. Addressing the awardees at the maiden ceremony at the plush Novotel Hotel, Accra Ghana. Mr. Oliver Alawuba, MD/CEO on behalf of management expressed his heartfelt gratitude and congratulations to the winners. Mr. Alawuba   encouraged the winners to constantly pursue excellence in any given task since that will elevate them above our day to day banking.

  He further opined that “to succeed in your chosen career in banking, you have to focus on the goal, which is to accomplish all your given tasks successfully.” He concluded by asking the proud recipients not to relent on their oars but to strive to achieve greater heights.

Accra Central came first with an overall score of 95% closely followed by East Legon 1 and Ring Road Business Offices with 94% and 87% respectively whilst Treasury on the other hand won Best Head Office Department with a score of 79 points.

29
October
UBA GHANA UNVEILS 7 MVPS for 2012
The management of UBA Ghana last Friday celebrated seven Most Valuable Personnel (MVP) awardees for the 2012 financial year at a cocktail reception held in their honour at the Executive Wing of the Head office. 

This year’s award ceremony which is the second celebrations after the maiden event in 2012 had seven award winners namely; 
•Adelaide  Valarie Tettey 
•Hasana Sesay
•Edem Gawuga
•Richard Doku
•Iddrisu Iddrisu
•Aurelia Odame
•Sarah Osei
Mr. Edem Gawuga and Miss. Aurellia Odame emerged as second time winners (Double Most Valuable Personnel’s )

For their excellent performance during the year under review, the awardees were each presented with an undisclosed cash amount in addition to a special pin to adorn the lapel of their jackets as a sign of distinguished performance. The MD/CEO elated at the caliber of staff represented at the ceremony, stated that the drive and passion that these few have shown in their commitment to excellence in their roles, is what has taken UBA Ghana to the position of Role Model in Africa.
He encouraged the new MVPs to keep up their drive to be the best in 2013, in view of the upcoming full year appraisal.
Mrs. Abiola Bawuah, DMD in her vote of thanks advised the proud recipients of the prestigious MVP pins not to relent on their oars but to strive to achieve greater heights in their respective chosen fields.

The UBA MVP award is a Human Resources initiative that rewards  excellent performance within the bank. 

07
October
Bank of Ghana Lauds UBA Ghana on Strong Risk Management Culture

The Governor, Dr. Henry Kofi Wampah, haspraised UBA Ghana, for instituting a robust risk management system which has led to zero infractions on regulatory provisions on the part of UBA Ghana.  Dr. Wampah said this while receiving the Group Managing Director, UBA Plc, Mr Phillips Oduoza, in his office in Accra.

He commended the pivotal role played by UBA in deepening financial inclusion and providing funds to critical sectors of the Ghanaian economy.  

The Governor called on UBA to organise seminars and workshop on risk management for indigenous financial institutions in the country to help build a strong risk management culture in Ghanaian financial institutions. He also called on UBA to support government’s policy on import substitution, aimed at growing the economy by increasing the volume of exports, through encouraging the production of locally made goods.

While thanking the Governor for the regulatory institution’s recognition of the Bank’s robust risk management policies, Phillips Oduoza, the Group Managing Director of UBA Plc said, “UBA being a global bank and the only African bank operating in United States, a geography noted for its strict control system, means that it has to institute a best in class risk management practices across its pan-African banking operations.” Oduoza emphasized the commitment of UBA to the development of Africa. “As an African institution, we understand the dimensions and characteristics of the continent’s financial landscape. It is our conviction that for the continent to grow, its indigenous financial institutions, like ours, with necessary wherewithal, should champion it. This is what we are doing in 18 African countries where we operate,” Oduoza said. He informed the Governor that UBA’s operation in Ghana remains its flagship on the continent, largely due to “the social economic and political stability the country offers to investors. We are most encouraged by the stable economic policies offered by Bank of Ghana. Our Bank has reaped immensely from the stability and we hope other countries on the continent will take a cue from Ghana.”

The UBA Group remains a highly diversified financial services provider with operations in 19 African countries, New York , London and Paris. It has over the years , built a strong retail franchise across the continent , offering its more than seven million customers , a bouquet of products and services tailored to meet their different financial needs .

August
UBA Ghana Celebrates 2012/2013 National Service Persons

UBA Ghana on last Friday August 9, 2013 held a send off reception in honour of its National Service Persons who have completed the service period with the bank at the Executive Wing.

In his welcome address the MD/CEO Mr. Oliver Alawuba mentioned that this batch of service personnel did excel in their respective roles and functions during the service period. “I am happy to announce that some of you are coming back to start a career with us”, he stated. 

He further advised the personnel to always be dutiful and abide by the tenets  of UBA’s core values in their respective chosen careers.

The 24 personnel  for the 2012/2013 service period were very excited as they received their  meritorious certificates from the MD/CEO. 




Chief Country Inspector Mr Ben Ahulu ( far left),Head of HCM, Mrs. Ackon, MD/CEO Mr Oliver Alawuba and CBO Branch Manager Belinda Tinkorang in a group Photograph

07
August
UBA Ghana opens Spintex branch Redshop

UBA Ghana last Friday launched its newest Redshop at  the Spintex branch  in Accra.

The Redshop operates as a separate banking hall solely for remittances from broad through Moneygram, Western Union and Africash.

“UBA is today providing another safe,  quick and stress-free mode of receiving remittances in less than five minutes at our Redshop” Deputy Managing Director Mrs. Abiola Bawuah espoused. Explaining further, Mrs. Bawuah stated that the model of the Redshop in selected localities in Ghana was based on closeness to ideal target market of receivers, visibility at street level and other areas’. Our aim is to alleviate the congestion, stress and frustration recipients of remittances go through on daily basis to receive money from relatives and friends from abroad, as well as provide an unmatched and dedicated services to the recipients of foreign inflows” Mrs. Bawuah added.

Chief Solomon Odemoro CEO of Solodem Company , a patron of the branch remarked that he was delighted that The Redshop had come to provide prompt, reliable and fast payment in not more than five minutes. He congratulated management for providing such solution for customers of the bank.


L-R

Abiola Bawuah (Mrs) DMD, UBA Ghana, Chief Ojariefe Solomon Odemoro, CEO of Solodems Company Limited and Nelly Abotchie (Mrs) Regional Director, UBA Ghana

03
July
Uba Ghana Fetes African Diplomats in Ghana
UBA Ghana last Friday hosted the diplomatic community in Ghana to a sumptuous buffet dinner at the lush Labadi Beach hotel here in Accra.

The event which was co-hosted by the Nigerian High Commissioner to Ghana attracted the Minister of State for Finance at the Presidency, African diplomats and their spouses and other friendly diplomatic missions. Also in attendance were Board Members of UBA Ghana, EXCO and selected captains of industry.

The Board Chairman of UBA Ghana, Mr. Kwame Pianim in his opening remarks chronicled the Groups Pan-African agenda and the exploits of UBA Ghana in particular.
He catalogued the many successes chalked by the bank in Ghana and thanked the dignitaries for their support.

H.E. Ademola Onafowokan, the Nigerian High Commissioner to Ghana elucidated his relationship with UBA which dates 32 years back. The High Commissioner who was full of praise for UBA encouraged his colleagues in the diplomatic community to bank with UBA.
Mr. Oliver Alawuba, the MD/CEO commended the envoys for honouring the invitation and especially the Nigerian High Commissioner for his continuous support.

June
Uba Ghana partners Chartered Institute of Management Accountants with Africard
UBA Ghana has entered into a partnership with the Chartered Institute of Management Accountants (CIMA) to provide students and members with a very unique opportunity to seamlessly make secure online fees payment using Africard. 

At a the signing of the MOU, the Deputy Managing Director of UBA Ghana Mrs. Abiola Bawuah  gave the assurance that UBA will meet and exceed CIMA’s  desire to provide a reliable, secure and effective channel for its students and members to make online payments. 



31
May
UBA Ghana Launches Africard

UBA Ghana recently launched  Africard which is a visa-enabled re-loadable card to the Ghanaian public.  The card which uses A pin and a Chip offers maximum security as it enable users to make secure payments via the internet with a Verified By Visa  (VBV) and the value on the cardholder’s account remains intact when the card is misplaced or stolen.  The card is a better alternative to a bank account as it is not tied to any bank account but can be used  on over 1.9 million ATMs and 30 million Point of Sale (POS)  terminals in over 179 countries across the world.

Mr. Oliver Alawuba, MD/CEO in  his opening remarks  revealed that it was common knowledge the Ghana, in particular and Africa as a whole remained largely cash-based societies in spite of the introduction of new payments modes such as debit cards and ATMs however, with the introduction of Africard and its many advantages, “we do not have any more excuses but to enjoy the convenience and security of card usage” .

 “ Africard was in the furtherance of the bank’s commitment to bring world class, customer –driven banking services on the doorstep of as many Ghanaians as possible. The card  would offer convenience to clients as there was no need to visit banking halls to collect cash and opined that  “it allows you to travel without carrying large sums of cash or foreign currency as the card can be used  worldwide” He added.

The addition of the of Africard to the bank’s array of products, he explained was yet another manifestation of the bank’s responsiveness to the needs to the need of its customers,UBA Ghana is offering Ghanaians the opportunity to seamlessly transfer funds either for business or personal needs he concluded.

Mrs. Abiola Bawuah, DMD entreated the media to be strong advocates for Africard especially for the convenience and security it provides to both the banked and the un-banked within the society.

The Africard product is initially available in all 25 branches of UBA nationwide, while plans are far advanced to enter into agency agreement with credible organizations to bring the card even closer to the doorstep of customers.

May
UBA Ghana Welcome Back Promo
UBA Ghana has introduced a three month Welcome Back Campaign” which aims at offering customers the opportunity to reactive their in - active accounts with as little as GH¢1.00.
  • Customers with in-active current can therefore re-activate with as little as GHC1 and enjoy free C.O.T.
  • Customers with   in-active savings accounts will also enjoy additional interest when they re-activate with a minimum of GHC1.
Customers of the bank who re-activate their in-active accounts with as little as GHC1 stand the chance of enjoying free C.O.T or additional interest on their savings or current accounts.
